-- SK Innovation Plans Shutdown for Ulsan Crude Units in 2012
-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 2012-02-03T02:43:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/sk-innovation-plans-shutdown-for-ulsan-crude-units-in-2012.html
SK Innovation Co. (096770) , which owns  South
Korea ’s biggest oil refiner, plans to shut a crude-processing
unit at its Ulsan refinery for maintenance in March and another
one in October.  The refiner will idle the 240,000-barrel-a-day No. 4 crude-
distillation unit in Ulsan for 34 days starting March 20,
according to a statement by the  Seoul-based company . It will
shut the 110,000-barrel-a-day No. 2 crude-distillation unit at
the refinery for 30 days starting Oct. 11.  SK Innovation owns oil refiner SK Energy Co., chemical
maker SK Global Chemical Co. and lubricant maker SK Lubricant.  The following is a table showing SK’s maintenance plans at
its units.  To contact the reporter on this story:
